    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Previous names",
            "shortText": "<p><i>Clinus fucorum, Pavoclinus fucorum.</i></p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_9_3505",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Characteristic body shape, being very laterally compressed with a short, steeply inclined head. The tall dorsal fin originates far forwards, almost above the eyes, and is expanded anteriorly into a large, rounded crest formed by the first five spines, but with no notch in the membrane behind this crest. The dorsal fin has 28–31 spines and 4–6 rays. Body colour fairly uniform green, yellow or dark brown, often pale patches on fins and a white patch beneath base of pectoral fin.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_3506",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Up to at least 20 cm total length, some sources report 30 cm.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_3507",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to South Africa.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> False Bay to Eastern Cape.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_3508",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>A rare species usually associated with kelps and other algae. No other details known.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_3509",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": [
                {
